de.weltraumschaf.juberblog

Class Preprocessor

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.weltraumschaf.juberblog.Preprocessor

  • public class Preprocessor
extends Object
    Parses all blocks of preprocessor code. Preprocessor blocks are opened by <?juberblog and closed by ?>. Between these markers key value pairs are recognized. The blocks are removed. Example: 
     ...
 >?juberblog
   key1: value1
   key2: value2
   // ...
   keyN: valueN
 ?<
 ...
    Author:
    Sven Strittmatter

      • recognizedData

        static void recognizedData(List<String> preprocesorBlocks,
                  Map<String,String> map)
        Recognizes key value pairs. Recognized key value pairs will be added to passed map. Lines with errors (no key/value or empty key) line is skipped and warning logged. Empty values are logged but not skipped.
        Parameters:
        preprocesorBlocks - must not be null
        map - must not be null
